Phase 6: AI Solution Design Agent

## Overview
A conversational agent that accepts a user's problem description and generates
an AI solution design by matching against the Case Library. Since we don't have
AWS credentials, we use keyword-based similarity matching instead of embeddings.

## How It Works
1. User describes their problem/scenario in a text box
2. Backend searches the Case Library for similar cases using keyword matching
   (TF-IDF style scoring across title, problem statement, solution description,
   AI technique, and tools/services fields)
3. Agent generates a structured solution design based on matched cases:
   - Recommended AI technique(s) — drawn from top matching cases
   - Reference cases — links to similar initiatives in the library
   - Suggested tools/services — based on what worked for similar cases
   - Estimated effort — averaged from matched cases' dev_time_hours
   - Expected outcomes — projected metrics based on similar cases
   - Implementation steps — generated from matched case patterns
4. User can refine by asking follow-up questions (session-based context)

## API Endpoints
- POST /agent/design
  - Body: { "query": "describe your problem...", "session_id": null }
  - Returns: { "session_id": "...", "design": { ... }, "matched_cases": [...] }
- POST /agent/followup
  - Body: { "session_id": "...", "question": "what about scaling?" }
  - Returns: { "answer": "...", "updated_design": { ... } }

## Frontend: "AI Agent" Tab
- Chat-style interface with input box at bottom
- First message triggers solution design generation
- Design displayed as structured card (technique, tools, effort, steps)
- Matched cases shown as clickable references
- Follow-up messages refine the design
- "New Conversation" button to reset

## Similarity Matching (No AWS Required)
- Tokenize query and case text fields into keywords
- Score each case by keyword overlap (weighted by field importance):
  - problem_statement: weight 3x
  - use_case_title: weight 2x
  - solution_description: weight 2x
  - ai_technique: weight 2x
  - tools_services: weight 1x
- Return top 3-5 matching cases
- Generate design recommendations from matched case data

## Future Enhancement (When Bedrock Available)
- Replace keyword matching with embedding-based semantic search
- Replace rule-based design generation with LLM (Claude) generation
- Add conversational memory via Bedrock's conversation API
